{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17601021","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17601021"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:11:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:11:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15646"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15646","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15646"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.84,0,0,0.05,0.11]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8337"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66482"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8337","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8337"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15646"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51935"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"183"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"2718"},{"type":"tags","id":"3549"},{"type":"tags","id":"3564"},{"type":"tags","id":"3604"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7010"},{"type":"tags","id":"8133"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20109"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20111"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22242"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66482","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66482"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 32-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-month history of progressive fatigue, dizziness on standing, and salt cravings. She has lost 4 kg in weight over this period. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination, she appears unwell. Her pulse rate is 95/min, blood pressure 95/65 mmHg supine and 80/50 mmHg standing, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 36.7\u00b0C. There is generalised hyperpigmentation of her skin, particularly in the palmar creases, buccal mucosa and back of her hands (Image).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA short synacthen test is performed with the following results:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBaseline cortisol: 85 nmol/L (200-700)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E30-minute cortisol: 95 nmol/L (\u0026gt;550)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E60-minute cortisol: 90 nmol/L (\u0026gt;550)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Addison\u0027s disease","Chronic fatigue syndrome","Depression","Hypothyroidism","Secondary adrenal insufficiency"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with classic features of primary adrenal insufficiency (Addison\u0027s disease), including postural hypotension, fatigue, salt craving, and weight loss. The characteristic hyperpigmentation occurs due to elevated adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH) levels. The short synacthen test confirms the diagnosis, showing minimal cortisol response to synthetic ACTH stimulation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAddison\u0027s disease\u003C/strong\u003E is characterised by primary adrenal insufficiency, where the adrenal glands fail to produce adequate cortisol. The diagnosis is confirmed by a short synacthen test showing inadequate cortisol response to ACTH stimulation, as seen in this case. The presence of hyperpigmentation specifically suggests primary rather than secondary adrenal insufficiency.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESecondary adrenal insufficiency\u003C/strong\u003E occurs due to pituitary ACTH deficiency. These patients typically have low cortisol but do not develop hyperpigmentation as ACTH levels are low. They may have a similar cortisol response to synacthen but without the characteristic skin changes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChronic fatigue syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E can present with fatigue but would not cause postural hypotension, hyperpigmentation, or abnormal synacthen test results. These patients typically have normal physical examination findings.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDepression\u003C/strong\u003E may cause fatigue and weight loss but would not explain the postural hypotension, hyperpigmentation, or abnormal cortisol response to synacthen.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypothyroidism\u003C/strong\u003E can cause fatigue and weight gain, but not weight loss or postural hypotension. Thyroid function tests would be abnormal, and the synacthen test would be normal.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A short synacthen test showing minimal cortisol response is diagnostic of primary adrenal insufficiency (Addison\u0027s disease).","Common presenting features of Addison\u0027s disease include postural hypotension, fatigue, and skin hyperpigmentation.","Primary adrenal insufficiency requires urgent glucocorticoid replacement therapy."],"references":["Mosca AM, Barbosa M, Ara\u00fajo R, Santos MJ. Addison\u0027s Disease: A Diagnosis Easy to Overlook. Cureus. 2021 Feb 15;13(2):e13364. doi: 10.7759/cureus.13364. PMID: 33747659; PMCID: PMC7970155.","Sherlock M, Stewart PM. The Short Synacthen Test and Its Utility in Assessing Recovery of Adrenal Function in Patients With Central Adrenal Insufficiency. J Clin Endocrinol Metab. 2019 Jan 1;104(1):17-20. doi: 10.1210/jc.2018-01317. PMID: 30085278; PMCID: PMC6260064.","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes. Oxford University Press, USA."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51935"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15646"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21269"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21269","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21269"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/0cmDykhtnmM6OzGnWXItsWsQdSDebz.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/0cmDykhtnmM6OzGnWXItsWsQdSDebz.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1024,"height":768}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51935","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51935"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-30T16:11:00+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-30T16:12:54+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8337"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66482"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66",